Step 1: Identify the key data  
• Total Revenue from the income statement is 22,876,677.56.  
• Total Assets (end amount) from the balance sheet is 33,082,821.36.

Step 2: Apply the Total Asset Turnover Ratio formula  
Total Asset Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue / Total Assets  
= 22,876,677.56 / 33,082,821.36

Step 3: Calculate the ratio  
When dividing, 22,876,677.56 divided by 33,082,821.36 ≈ 0.691. Rounding to two decimal places gives approximately 0.69.

Thus, the Total Asset Turnover Ratio is approximately 0.69.

Final answer in JSON format:

{"solution": {"Total Asset Turnover Ratio": "0.69"}}
